title.narrative: Strengthened partnerships, policy, planning, governance, capacity and accountability of education authorities to deliver quality pre-primary and basic education (Grades 1-10) for all children (ages 5-18) in Jordan.

description.narrative: UNICEF has improved access to quality education for all vulnerable children in Jordan, including refugees. Since March, UNICEF has supported the Ministry of Education to provide children aged 5 to 18 years with access to blended learning – including innovative approaches to bridging the digital divide for the most vulnerable – whilst ensuring that investments in the COVID-19 response also improve the long-term resilience and quality of the education system. Interventions have been disability inclusive and gender responsive, whilst focused on improving learning outcomes and wellbeing of children in both formal and non-formal education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/08/2020
